comment: MM printing set-up: homing all positions with 1.9 mm glasses on positions 1 and 4 (material positions). Placing all vats (three metal vats, 3D-printed plastic carrier with ceramic sponge). Vol.: 500 µL T2; 500 µL T1. Pause after layer 1 and washing/dapping: printed structures (stalks) connected -> print aborted.

Inks from printrun 1. Still too much overcuring between printed stalks. Dapping insufficient: too much liquid left around prints. Print aborted after layer 3. Both scaffolds collected in DPBS and microscoped. Then incubation in DPBS with 5K U/mL lysozyme.
